cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the topology of the Internet at the autonomous system level.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses the properties of synthetic graphs generated by power law topology models.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper touches upon the redundancy and robustness of the Internet topology.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the Internet topology is relevant to network security and the paper may discuss any vulnerabilities or attacks on the network.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on algorithms or data structures, but rather on the comparison of real and synthetic graphs.
